
Important notes:
-----------------

1)Data types:
     	integer-short,long,signed,unsigned,int
	char   - signed,unsigned
  	Real   - float,double,long double

2)Storage class signifies 4 things:
	1)Storage
	2)Default value
	3)Scope
	4)Life

3)Automatic storage class:
  	Default value : garbage
	storage	      : Memory
	scope	      : local to the block
	Life 	      : till controls is in the block in which
                        variable is defined

4)Register storage class:
	Default value : garbage
	storage	      : CPU registers
	scope         : local to the block
	Life	      : till control is in the block in which variable is
                        defined.
5)Static storage class:
	Default value : 0
	Storage       : memory
	scope         : Local to the block
	Life 	      : Till execution of program doesn't end

6)Extern storage class:
	Default value : 0
	Storage       : memory
	Scope         : Global
	Life 	      : Till execution of program doesn't end

7)Redeclaration of variable is ok,redefintion is not
	int i;---->Definition       extern int i;---->Declaration
